!! Q/A
''Q:'' What's the difference from fellowship and Biblical friendship? Some of these passages that we see are in context of the church or fellow believers. So are all believers in biblical friendships.

They are pretty similar if you look at them in practice. Those are all things that if two or more people are involved then I think that it can involve into biblical friendship.

Intimacy of biblical friendship. Christ had intimate friends. David and Jonathan. Galatians 3. Psalm 139:1-4 & Genesis 3 or 4. Back in the day, when you say know someone, it is saying that you have a climax of intimacy with a person.

"Q:" Seems like Luke 5:18-19 is talking about a possible non-believer. How does this apply to Biblical friendship? Is it because of verse 20 where we see that Christ saw their faith?

We see this that this is just a case where friends are going at a decent length and Christ appeared to be in town at the time. It gives like an example for someone in their context.